headline: 'Like Joan of Arc': Marthe Robin, the recluse who sought to 'raise France up again'
description: 'Marthe Robin, Saint or Fraud?' (2/5). In the 1930s, the Catholic mystic, whose words became increasingly political, started developing the Foyers de Charité, a spiritual and educational organization aimed at fostering France's spiritual renewal.

headline: A winemaker, his daughter and a vintage for their undocumented workers
description: In southeastern France, Philippe Grisard and his daughter, Nadège, rely daily on undocumented workers to help tend their vineyard. To draw attention to their workers' precarious legal status, they named one of their vintages 'Sans eux' ('Without Them').

headline: AI, my students and me: 'Last semester marks the nadir of my experience in academia'
description: 'Letters from America' (1/6). The writer and journalist Thomas Chatterton Williams has been startled by the omnipresence of artificial intelligence at university, which he believes threatens the very foundations of education and our ability to think.
